Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2016. 

Truett-Hurst, Inc. Key Developments

Truett-Hurst, Inc. Elects Spencer Grimes as Class I Director
May 23 17
At the 2016 Annual Meeting held on May 19, 2017 the stockholders of the Truett-Hurst, Inc. elected Spencer Grimes as Class I director to serve until the 2019 annual meeting of stockholders and thereafter until his successor is duly elected and qualified.


Truett-Hurst, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended March 31, 2017
May 11 17
Truett-Hurst, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company’s net sales were USD 5,340,000 against USD 4,906,000 a year ago. Income from operations was USD 141,000 against loss from operations of USD 29,000 a year ago. Net income before income taxes was USD 56,000 against loss before income taxes of USD 182,000 a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was USD 33,000 or USD 0.01 per basic share against net loss attributable to the company of USD 93,000 or USD 0.02 per diluted share a year ago. Net income from continuing operations was USD 55,000 against net loss from continuing operations of USD 183,000 a year ago. 

For the nine months, the company’s net sales were USD 16,962,000 against USD 19,780,000 a year ago. Loss from operations was USD 158,000 against income from operations of USD 329,000 a year ago. Net income before income taxes was USD 539,000 against loss of USD 61,000 a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was USD 303,000 or USD 0.04 per diluted share against net loss attributable to the company of USD 72,000 or USD 0.02 per diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was USD 3,040,000 against USD 2,659,000 a year ago. Acquisition of property and equipment was USD 473,000 against USD 395,000 a year ago. Acquisition of intangible and other assets was USD 31,000 against USD 125,000 a year ago. Net income from continuing operations was USD 537,000 against loss of USD 62,000 a year ago.


Truett-Hurst, Inc. to Report Q3, 2017 Results on May 11, 2017
May 9 17
Truett-Hurst, Inc. announced that they will report Q3, 2017 results at 1:00 PM, GMT Standard Time on May 11, 2017


